Opportunity Insights Economic Tracker (OIET) Data Analytics - I (Employment Changes)¶

Author: Debanjan Saha¶

Affiliation: Northeastern University, Boston, MA¶

Description:¶

The Opportunity Insights Economic Tracker aggregates anonymised data from prominent private enterprises ranging from credit card processors to payroll service providers. The goal is to present a real-time view of variables such as unemployment, consumer spending, and job advertisements across counties, industries, and income levels.

In this notebook we will try to summarize the findings by visualizing various changes in employment patterns across the United States in various levels of granularity.

Data Source and Data Dictionary:¶

The data is open-sourced and readily available in the OIET GitHub Repo

November 2020. Available at: https://opportunityinsights.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/tracker_paper.pdf

def employment_by_quartile(dataset, typ='actual'):
    """
    Plot Employment Change across four income groups:
    emp_incq1 -- income: <$27,000
    emp_incq2 -- income: $27,000-$37,000
    emp_incq3 -- income: $37,000-$60,000
    emp_incq4 -- income: >$60,000

    :params dataset: Dataset which contains the data for plotting
    :params typ: 'actual' contains the real income levels provided
                 'pct' contains the percentage change in income
    :return: None -> plots
    """
    fig, axs =  plt.subplots(2, 2, figsize = (20, 8), sharex=True)
    if typ == 'actual':
        sns.lineplot(x='date_ts', y='emp_incq1', data=dataset, color='g', ax=axs[0][0])
        axs[0][0].tick_params(labelrotation = 35)
        axs[0][0].set_title("Employment levels for workers below bottom quartile (<$27,000)")
        sns.lineplot(x='date_ts', y='emp_incq2', data=dataset, color='b', ax=axs[0][1])
        axs[0][1].tick_params(labelrotation = 35)
        axs[0][1].set_title("Employment levels for workers in second quartile ($27,000-$37,000)")
        sns.lineplot(x='date_ts', y='emp_incq3', data=dataset, color='y', ax=axs[1][0])
        axs[1][0].tick_params(labelrotation = 35)
        axs[1][0].set_title("Employment levels for workers in third quartile ($37,000-$60,000)")
        sns.lineplot(x='date_ts', y='emp_incq4', data=dataset, color='r', ax=axs[1][1])
        axs[1][1].tick_params(labelrotation = 35)
        axs[1][1].set_title("Employment levels for workers in top quartile (>$60,000)")
        plt.tight_layout()
        
    if typ == 'pct':
        sns.lineplot(x='date_ts', y='pct_emp_incq1', data=dataset, color='g', ax=axs[0][0])
        axs[0][0].tick_params(labelrotation = 35)
        axs[0][0].set_title("Pecentage employment change for workers below bottom quartile (<$27,000)")
        sns.lineplot(x='date_ts', y='pct_emp_incq2', data=dataset, color='b', ax=axs[0][1])
        axs[0][1].tick_params(labelrotation = 35)
        axs[0][1].set_title("Pecentage employment change for workers in second quartile ($27,000-$37,000)")
        sns.lineplot(x='date_ts', y='pct_emp_incq3', data=dataset, color='y', ax=axs[1][0])
        axs[1][0].tick_params(labelrotation = 35)
        axs[1][0].set_title("Pecentage employment change for workers in third quartile ($37,000-$60,000)")
        sns.lineplot(x='date_ts', y='pct_emp_incq4', data=dataset, color='r', ax=axs[1][1])
        axs[1][1].tick_params(labelrotation = 35)
        axs[1][1].set_title("Pecentage employment change for workers in top quartile (>$60,000)")

    fig.suptitle("Employment Change across Income Groups", fontsize=15, va="bottom")
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()

def employment_by_median(dataset, typ = 'actual'):
    """
    Plot Employment Change across the middle of Income Distribution:
    emp_incbelowmed -- income: <$27,000
    emp_incmiddle   -- income: $27,000-$60,000
    emp_incabovemed -- income: >$60,000

    :params dataset: Dataset which contains the data for plotting
    :params typ: 'actual' contains the real income levels provided
                 'pct' contains the percentage change in income
    :return: None -> plots
    """
    fig, axs =  plt.subplots(3, 1, figsize = (8, 12), sharex=True)
    if typ == 'actual':
        sns.lineplot(x='date_ts', y='emp_incmiddle', data=dataset, color='g', ax=axs[0])
        axs[0].tick_params(labelrotation = 35)
        axs[0].set_title("Employment levels of workers in two middle quartiles ($27,000-$60,000)")
        sns.lineplot(x='date_ts', y='emp_incbelowmed', data=dataset, color='b', ax=axs[1])
        axs[1].tick_params(labelrotation = 35)
        axs[1].set_title("Employment levels of workers in the bottom half (<$37,000)")
        sns.lineplot(x='date_ts', y='emp_incabovemed', data=dataset, color='r', ax=axs[2])
        axs[2].tick_params(labelrotation = 35)
        axs[2].set_title("Employment levels of workers in the top half (>$37,000)")
    if typ == 'pct':
        sns.lineplot(x='date_ts', y='pct_emp_incmid', data=dataset, color='g', ax=axs[0])
        axs[0].tick_params(labelrotation = 35)
        axs[0].set_title("Percentage employment change for workers in two middle quartiles ($27,000-$60,000)")
        sns.lineplot(x='date_ts', y='pct_emp_incbmed', data=dataset, color='b', ax=axs[1])
        axs[1].tick_params(labelrotation = 35)
        axs[1].set_title("Percentage employment change for workers in the bottom half (<$37,000)")
        sns.lineplot(x='date_ts', y='pct_emp_incamed', data=dataset, color='r', ax=axs[2])
        axs[2].tick_params(labelrotation = 35)
        axs[2].set_title("Perentage employment change for workers in the top half (>$37,000)")

    fig.suptitle("Employment Change across the middle of Income Distribution", fontsize=15, va="bottom")
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()

def employment_by_industry(dataset, typ='actual'):
    """
    Plot Employment Change across different Industries by NAICS supersector:
    emp_ss40 -- workers in trade, transportation and utilities (NAICS supersector 40)
    emp_ss60 -- workers in professional and business services (NAICS supersector 60)
    emp_ss65 -- workers in education and health services (NAICS supersector 65)
    emp_ss70 -- workers in leisure and hospitality (NAICS supersector 70)

    :params dataset: Dataset which contains the data for plotting
    :params typ: 'actual' contains the real income levels provided
                 'pct' contains the percentage change in income
    :return: None -> plots
    """
    fig, axs =  plt.subplots(2, 2, figsize = (20, 8), sharex=True)
    if typ == 'actual':
        sns.lineplot(x='date_ts', y='emp_ss40', data=dataset, color='g', ax=axs[0][0])
        axs[0][0].tick_params(labelrotation = 35)
        axs[0][0].set_title("Employment levels for workers in trade, transportation and utilities (NAICS supersector 40)")
        sns.lineplot(x='date_ts', y='emp_ss60', data=dataset, color='b', ax=axs[0][1])
        axs[0][1].tick_params(labelrotation = 35)
        axs[0][1].set_title("Employment levels for workers in professional and business services NAICS supersector 60)")
        sns.lineplot(x='date_ts', y='emp_ss65', data=dataset, color='y', ax=axs[1][0])
        axs[1][0].tick_params(labelrotation = 35)
        axs[1][0].set_title("Employment levels for workers in education and health services (NAICS supersector 65)")
        sns.lineplot(x='date_ts', y='emp_ss70', data=dataset, color='r', ax=axs[1][1])
        axs[1][1].tick_params(labelrotation = 35)
        axs[1][1].set_title("Employment levels for workers in leisure and hospitality (NAICS supersector 70)")
        
    if typ == 'pct':
        sns.lineplot(x='date_ts', y='pct_emp_incss40', data=dataset, color='g', ax=axs[0][0])
        axs[0][0].tick_params(labelrotation = 35)
        axs[0][0].set_title("Percentage employment change for workers in trade, transportation and utilities (NAICS supersector 40)")
        sns.lineplot(x='date_ts', y='pct_emp_incss60', data=dataset, color='b', ax=axs[0][1])
        axs[0][1].tick_params(labelrotation = 35)
        axs[0][1].set_title("Percentage employment change for workers in professional and business services NAICS supersector 60)")
        sns.lineplot(x='date_ts', y='pct_emp_incss65', data=dataset, color='y', ax=axs[1][0])
        axs[1][0].tick_params(labelrotation = 35)
        axs[1][0].set_title("Percentage employment change for workers in education and health services (NAICS supersector 65)")
        sns.lineplot(x='date_ts', y='pct_emp_incss70', data=dataset, color='r', ax=axs[1][1])
        axs[1][1].tick_params(labelrotation = 35)
        axs[1][1].set_title("Percentage employment change for workers in leisure and hospitality (NAICS supersector 70)")
        
    fig.suptitle("Employment Change across different Industries", fontsize=15, va="bottom")
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()

def employment_unweighted(dataset, typ='actual'):
    """
    Plot Employment Change in Country x Industry with non-zero employment across all four quartiles:
    emp_subset_unweighted_q1 -- workers with income: <$27,000
    emp_subset_unweighted_q2 -- workers with income: $27,000-$37,000
    emp_subset_unweighted_q3 -- workers with income: $37,000-$60,000
    emp_subset_unweighted_q4 -- workers with income: >$60,000

    :params dataset: Dataset which contains the data for plotting
    :params typ: 'actual' contains the real income levels provided
                 'pct' contains the percentage change in income
    :return: None -> plots
    """
    fig, axs =  plt.subplots(2, 2, figsize = (20, 8), sharex=True)
    if typ == 'actual':
        sns.lineplot(x='date_ts', y='emp_subset_unweighted_q1', data=dataset, color='g', ax=axs[0][0])
        axs[0][0].tick_params(labelrotation = 35)
        axs[0][0].set_title("Non-zero employment levels for workers below bottom quartile (<$27,000)")
        sns.lineplot(x='date_ts', y='emp_subset_unweighted_q2', data=dataset, color='b', ax=axs[0][1])
        axs[0][1].tick_params(labelrotation = 35)
        axs[0][1].set_title("Non-zero employment levels for workers in second quartile ($27,000-$37,000)")
        sns.lineplot(x='date_ts', y='emp_subset_unweighted_q3', data=dataset, color='y', ax=axs[1][0])
        axs[1][0].tick_params(labelrotation = 35)
        axs[1][0].set_title("Non-zero employment levels for workers in third quartile ($37,000-$60,000)")
        sns.lineplot(x='date_ts', y='emp_subset_unweighted_q4', data=dataset, color='r', ax=axs[1][1])
        axs[1][1].tick_params(labelrotation = 35)
        axs[1][1].set_title("Non-zero employment levels for workers in top quartile (>$60,000)")
        plt.tight_layout()
        
    if typ == 'pct':
        sns.lineplot(x='date_ts', y='pct_emp_uwgtq1', data=dataset, color='g', ax=axs[0][0])
        axs[0][0].tick_params(labelrotation = 35)
        axs[0][0].set_title("Pecentage employment change for workers below bottom quartile (<$27,000)")
        sns.lineplot(x='date_ts', y='pct_emp_uwgtq2', data=dataset, color='b', ax=axs[0][1])
        axs[0][1].tick_params(labelrotation = 35)
        axs[0][1].set_title("Pecentage employment change for workers in second quartile ($27,000-$37,000)")
        sns.lineplot(x='date_ts', y='pct_emp_uwgtq3', data=dataset, color='y', ax=axs[1][0])
        axs[1][0].tick_params(labelrotation = 35)
        axs[1][0].set_title("Pecentage employment change for workers in third quartile ($37,000-$60,000)")
        sns.lineplot(x='date_ts', y='pct_emp_uwgtq4', data=dataset, color='r', ax=axs[1][1])
        axs[1][1].tick_params(labelrotation = 35)
        axs[1][1].set_title("Pecentage employment change for workers in top quartile (>$60,000)")

    fig.suptitle("Employment Change in Country x Industry with non-zero employment", fontsize=15, va="bottom")
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()

def employment_reweighted(dataset, typ = 'actual'):
    """
    Plot Employment Change for workers in various quartiles reweighting to match 
    the county x industry (2-digit NAICS code) distribution of workers:
    emp_subset_reweighted_q1 -- workers with income: <$27,000
    emp_subset_reweighted_q2 -- workers with income: $27,000-$60,000
    emp_subset_reweighted_q3 -- workers with income: >$60,000

    :params dataset: Dataset which contains the data for plotting
    :params typ: 'actual' contains the real income levels provided
                 'pct' contains the percentage change in income
    :return: None -> plots
    """
    fig, axs =  plt.subplots(3, 1, figsize = (8, 12), sharex=True)
    if typ == 'actual':
        sns.lineplot(x='date_ts', y='emp_subset_reweighted_q1', data=dataset, color='g', ax=axs[0])
        axs[0].tick_params(labelrotation = 35)
        axs[0].set_title("Reweighted Employment levels of workers in the bottom quartile (<$27,000)")
        sns.lineplot(x='date_ts', y='emp_subset_reweighted_q2', data=dataset, color='b', ax=axs[1])
        axs[1].tick_params(labelrotation = 35)
        axs[1].set_title("Reweighted Employment levels of workers in the middle quartile ($27,000-$37,000)")
        sns.lineplot(x='date_ts', y='emp_subset_reweighted_q3', data=dataset, color='r', ax=axs[2])
        axs[2].tick_params(labelrotation = 35)
        axs[2].set_title("Reweighted Employment levels of workers in the third quartile (>$37,000)")
    if typ == 'pct':
        sns.lineplot(x='date_ts', y='pct_emp_rwgtq1', data=dataset, color='g', ax=axs[0])
        axs[0].tick_params(labelrotation = 35)
        axs[0].set_title("Percentage reweighted employment change for workers in lowest quartile")
        sns.lineplot(x='date_ts', y='pct_emp_rwgtq2', data=dataset, color='b', ax=axs[1])
        axs[1].tick_params(labelrotation = 35)
        axs[1].set_title("Percentage reweighted employment change for workers in the second quartile")
        sns.lineplot(x='date_ts', y='pct_emp_rwgtq3', data=dataset, color='r', ax=axs[2])
        axs[2].tick_params(labelrotation = 35)
        axs[2].set_title("Percentage reweighted employment change for workers in the third quartile")

    fig.suptitle("Reweighted Employment Change across the Income Distribution", fontsize=15, va="bottom")
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()

def employment_retail_food(dataset, typ='actual'):
    """
    Plot Employment Change for workers in Retail (NAICS sector 44-45) and 
    Accomodation and Food Services (NAICS sector 72):
    emp_retail -- workers in Retail (NAICS sector 44-45)
    emp_s72    -- workers in Accomodation and Food Services (NAICS sector 72)
    
    :params dataset: Dataset which contains the data for plotting
    :params typ: 'actual' contains the real income levels provided
                 'pct' contains the percentage change in income
    :return: None -> plots
    """
    fig, axs =  plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize = (20, 6), sharex=True, squeeze=True)
    if typ == 'actual':
        sns.lineplot(x='date_ts', y='emp_retail', data=dataset, color='g', ax=axs[0])
        axs[0].tick_params(labelrotation = 35)
        axs[0].set_title("Employment levels for workers in retail")
        sns.lineplot(x='date_ts', y='emp_s72', data=dataset, color='b', ax=axs[1])
        axs[1].tick_params(labelrotation = 35)
        axs[1].set_title("Employment level for workers in accommodation and food services (NAICS sector 72)")
        plt.tight_layout()
        
    if typ == 'pct':
        sns.lineplot(x='date_ts', y='pct_emp_rtl', data=dataset, color='g', ax=axs[0])
        axs[0].tick_params(labelrotation = 35)
        axs[0].set_title("Pecentage employment change for workers in retail")
        sns.lineplot(x='date_ts', y='pct_emp_incs72', data=dataset, color='b', ax=axs[1])
        axs[1].tick_params(labelrotation = 35)
        axs[1].set_title("Pecentage employment change for workers in accommodation and food services (NAICS sector 72)")
        
    fig.suptitle("Employment Change in Employment for Retail, Accomodation and Food Services", fontsize=15, va="bottom")
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()

def employment_retail_quarters(dataset, typ = 'actual'):
    """
    Plot Employment Change for workers in Retail (NAICS sector 44-45):

        axs[2].tick_params(labelrotation = 35)
